ca.uhn.fhir.rest.annotation

Annotation Type Sort


  • @Target(value=PARAMETER)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Sort
    For searches, a parameter may be annotated with the Sort annotation. The parameter should be of type SortSpec.

    Note that if you wish to chain multiple sort parameters (i.e. a sub sort), you should use the SortSpec.setChain(SortSpec) method. Multiple parameters should not be annotated with the Sort annotation.

    See Also:
    Search
